text: Total confusion is how I would describe the staff... We had a group of seven, the hostess walks us around aimlessly for about 5 minutes, then takes us near a table for four, stands there, then turns and asks how many of us there are... Then just kind of walked off and left us at the table for only 4... So we saw two tables outside that were open and with enough seats there, so we asked one of the waitresses if we could sit there and they told us yes, finally... It was then another 20 minutes before a waitress showed up to take our drink orders a beer and water for everyone... We only EVER got 4 waters, and when we reminded her that we still needed 3 more when she brought out the first few people's beer, she disappeared for another 10 minutes, and finally came back with the last two people's beers, but still no waters. Then she said she would be right back to take our food order... She arrives back to our daily about 10 minutes later again... We now have been seated for 45 minutes and just finally getting asked about our food order. After that the meal was pretty fine, food was good, and we got our check shortly after that... But what we hoped would be a quick late lunch turned into an almost 2 hour affair.

text:
Camped here for two nights. BEAUTIFUL views as you can see from the pictures attached. Nice campsites with a covered shelter and picnic table at each site. A couple things to note though.
1. There is only one bathroom. It is at the south end of the campground and looks like it hasn't been updated in 30+ years. The shower stalls do not have shower curtains or rods.
2. There is a VERY busy highway 100-200 feet away from all of the campsites. A lot of LOUD diesel trucks ROAR by here at all hours of day and night. So BRING EARPLUGS if you would like to be able to sleep at night! Especially if you are tent camping! I forgot mine the first night and slept horribly. The 2nd night I had bought some and they blocked out all the noise and I slept much better.
3. Each covered shelter has a light socket. It may or may not have a light bulb already in it. So bring your own and you won't have to use a lantern. There are circuit breakers for each site that control the electricity.
4. There are a lot of biting ant hills around the campground. We took rocks from the fire ring and placed one by each ant hill in and around our campsite so we would be able to see be aware of them day and night.
5. The non-preferred campsites are just as nice and have just as great of views as the preferred campsites. So save yourself $5.

I took my wife here tonight for her Birthday. Sadly is wasn't one of out best experiences. My wife ordered her steak medium and it came out medium rare, my daughter ordered her steak medium well and it was just barely medium. I know you always have the option to send it back, who really wants to send food back to the kitchen. We had a server who had only been there two days. Once we got our food she NEVER came back and checked on us. Our drinks had been empty a while and I got another server to come over. She ended up taking care of us and did a great job, I believe her name was Tori. I always like to give new servers the benefit of the doubt, but we were this girls only table. We will be back, I love the lunch menu!

1/14/2020 Had an excellent lunch today, the catfish was good as usual an the steak soup is so good.

text: We went as guests to swim in the pool. $5 per person is great! I called head and found out the price and swim times. We got the about 5 minutes early. The paperwork they required took a full 25 minutes. And I was the only one the two ladies were helping. Already into our swim time, we changed quickly and went into the pool room only to be told they were at max capacity! Apparently the lifeguards are supposed to tell the front deck this but they "must have forgotten". We were told we could wait another 30 minutes until a party left and then maybe we could be admitted. No refund was offered. This was very disappointing to my children who were so excited to swim. We waited and were finally able to swim for 1/2 the time. However, if you can't pass a swim test, you have to stay in the baby section. No floaties are allowed with the "swimmers". This separated my 3 who wanted to play together and made my timid child feel left out. Overall not a great time.

text:
This Mazzios needs to clean house on their staff. Its deplorable!! I have been trying to buy pepperolies for a week and they are always out (at 5:30 or 6 in the evening). We came in at 6 and there were 2 other couples in there eating so they weren't busy. It took us forever to find a clean table and when the girl working there did finally come out and clean up I watched her wipe off 7 tables with the same rag and no cleaning solution!! Disgusting!! I have worked in restaurants and this is not acceptable. This should have been a clue when we pulled up to the restaurant the door to the kitchen was open to the outside and they were all standing around talking. The bathrooms were horrible as well. There was a bunch of hair in the sink of the ladies room and it looked like it hadn't been cleaned in months. The mens bathroom had no SOAP AND THE COOKS WERE MEN.
When we tried to place our order for the pepperolies and found out they were out again she never offered to tell us what the specials were to help us out. She was just a warm  body standing behind the counter. My husband ordered a salad and everything was low or out, the crackers were smashed and unusable. We ordered a thin crust pepperoni and it looked like a flatbread pizza, didnt know they had that. The cheese dippers were too brown and not tasty.
As we were leaving another couple came in and looked at the buffet and salad bar and left. Wish we wouldn't have wasted our money!
This is too bad because we love Mazzios but we wont be back to this one (and it's in our town)until they get better management.

I'll stay here until I find a permanent place to settle in the area,but I have to say as far as homeless people in the area,well the hotel has no control over where homeless people wonder too. text:
I have heard great things about their pizza and decided to order. The first time I ordered online, I got a lunch deal and they forgot the cookie and chips. An honest mistake. I didn’t worry about it. Ordered a second time the next week and they forgot them again. So that time I called and they replace the chips and cookies from both orders.
Ordered a 3rd time, 2 flatbreads and they game me 1 flatbread and a sandwich. Not even a Sandwhich with the ingredients I ordered on my pizza. I called and complained and they offered to remake my pizzas.
I waited 2 weeks and decided to call in for my remakes and once again they got it wrong. I asked for the chicken and avocado pizza with no red peppers. I got a chicken pizza with extra red pepper and no avocado. I ordered with a coworker and they messed up her order too this time.
At this point I’ve given up on them and I won’t be ordering again. Their food is good but they can’t seem to fill orders correctly and that’s frustrating. They can’t even do it correctly when they know they’re making a remake because it was screwed up the first time. I know I could probably call again and they’d offer me another remake but at this point I don’t trust them to do it correctly and I don’t want to waste the food or go hungry because I can’t eat what they made.
